raw_data.title: Management Analyst
raw_data.description: Supervises the execution of approaches for definition and design of complex IT related systems relative to task order under fiscal, organizational and other limitations. Designs and monitors schedules, performance benchmarks, and progress in alignment with project goals. Reviews progress and conducts quality assurance activities. May conduct organizational studies and evaluations, design systems and procedures, and conduct work simplification and measurement studies.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: 2 years of experience for one year of formal education

labor_categories.years_experience: 2 years of experience for one year of formal education

raw_data.title: Computer Systems Analyst
raw_data.description: The Computer Systems Analyst researches and evaluates new technologies to make recommendations to clients regarding systems requirements, upgrades, and ad hoc consultation based on project goals. Through consultation, the Computer Systems analyst identifies the organizational needs of IT systems, analyzes costs and benefits, creates plans, oversees installations, tests systems, and trains users as per task order goals. May develop new systems or work to update or improve current systems. Executes custom software approaches to solving client problems. Where complex systems are involved uses systems analysis techniques to evaluate alternative solutions.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: 2 years of experience for one year of formal education
